description_more: Result of "White Blood Cell Count" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. White blood count is the number of leukocytes.   Analyser operating range was 0 to 9x10^11 cells/Litre.   Typical reference range is 3.5x10^9 to 9.6x10^9 cells/Litre.
category: Biological samples > Assay results > Blood assays > Blood count

description_more: Result of "Red Blood Cell Count" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Red blood cells is the number of erythrocytes.   Analyser operating range was 0 to 2x10^13 cells/Litre.   Typical reference range is 3.9x10^12 to 5.5x10^12 cells/Litre.
category: Biological samples > Assay results > Blood assays > Blood count

description_more: Result of "Mean Corpuscular Haemoglobin" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit.

description_more: Result of "Lymphocytes Number" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Lymphocyte count is the proportion of ( lymphoctyes / 100 ) x white blood cell count

description_more: Result of "Basophils Number" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Basophils count is the proportion of ( basophils / 100 ) x white blood cell count.

description_more: ACE touchscreen question "How old were you when your periods stopped?" The following checks were performed:  If answer   If answer > Participants age then rejected  If answer > 70 then rejected  If answer   If answer > 60 then participant asked to confirm   If the participant activated the Help button they were shown the message:     If you are unsure, please provide an estimate or select Do not know.      ~F3581~ was collected from women who indicated that their periods had stopped, as defined by their answers to ~F2724~
category: UK Biobank Assessment Centre > Touchscreen > Sex-specific factors > Female-specific factors

description_more: ACE touchscreen question "What was your age when the blood clot in the leg (DVT) was first diagnosed?" The following checks were performed:  If answer   If answer > Participants age then rejected  If answer   If answer > 69 then participant asked to confirm   If the participant activated the Help button they were shown the message:     If you are unsure, please provide an estimate or select Do not know.      ~F4012~ was collected from participants who indicated they were told by a doctor that they have had a Blood clot in the leg (DVT) , as defined by their answers to ~F6152~
category: UK Biobank Assessment Centre > Touchscreen > Health and medical history > Medical conditions
